Veteran Nollywood actor, Jide Kosoko, on Tuesday announced the birth of another grandchild, born by his actress daughter, Abidemi Kosoko. On his Instagram page, the excited grandfather shared a picture of the child’s mother and the newborn. He further called on fans and colleagues to join him in thanking God for the safe delivery of the baby. The veteran actor said, “A big congratulations to the Kosoko and Bankole Families, as Abidek gave birth to a baby girl this morning; an addition to my grandchildren. “Join me in thanking God and prayers for the mother never to witness after birth sickness. Thank you my people.” The sister of the new mum, Sola Kosoko, also took to her Instagram page to express joy at the new addition to the family. She said, “A big congratulations to Kosoko and Bankole families on our new bundle of joy as my sister #bidemi_kosoko gave birth to a bouncing baby girl. Mother and daughter are well and sound.” Quoting a verse from the Holy Bible, Sola said, “Children are a gift from God, a fruit of the womb a reward.” Following the announcements, Nollywood stars, entertainers, and fans have taken to the comment sections of Jide, Sola, and Abidemi Kosoko, to congratulate the family. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com